One person was killed and another sustained critical
injuries when they crash on Nelson Mandela Drive in Universitas Bloemfontein. Trauma Response Africa spokesperson Stanley Schimper said in
a statement that jaws of life had to be used to free the driver before advanced
life support treatment was initiated by paramedics of various services. Schimper said he was then transported to the hospital for
further care in a critical condition. “Sadly, there was nothing more that could be done for the
passenger and he was declared deceased on the scene.” Cops opened an inquest docket and are be investigating the
accident further. 